g.text: Door, Room #2: The lieutenant's door is closed.
Interfacing: Doesn't he want to go for a little drive?
Logic: Is *he* not worried that you haven't found the murder weapon yet?
Door, Room #2: Your hear the sound of a drawer closing followed by the shuffling of feet.
Kim Kitsuragi: "What is it, officer?" The lieutenant's voice sounds tired.
"What is it, Harry? What time is it?" The lieutenant's voice sounds tired.
Electrochemistry: Where is he? Isn't it party o'clock?
Logic: Is *he* not worried that you might have missed something in the autopsy?
Door, Room #2: Your hear the sound of a drawer closing followed by the shuffling of feet.
"Is that you, Harry? What time is it?"
You: "Do you wanna go for a midnight drive, to clear our heads?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "To clear our heads from what, *sleep*?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Very funny. What do you want?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "Isn't it always party time with you?"
Esprit de Corps: You're going to have to figure this one out on your own.
Inland Empire: Anything to not face the hanged disco man yet...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Well, I don't know either. You should get some rest."
Esprit de Corps: Sleep is what he needs most right now.
You: "I wanted to go over the case again."
You: "I'm... not ready to go to sleep yet."
You: "It is I, Garte, Manager of this Faire Cafeterium."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You'll get used to them, I promise. Sometimes it helps to go for a short walk."
Logic: Is *he* not worried that you didn't get the body down?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, that's a good idea. Let's do it in the morning. You know, when we're not sleeping."
You: I should stop bothering Kim. [Leave.]
Door, Room #2: Your hear the sound of a drawer closing followed by the shuffling of feet.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, what is it? What time is it?"
You: Tap out the tune Kim whistled on the swing set.
